[call-toby] Telegram sent (info): Crushed coral is the classic low-intervention option — a small amount tucked into the filter or a mesh bag raises and buffers pH slowly without swings. Aragonite substrate mixed in or added to a filter sock works similarly. Both dissolve in response to acidity, so they're naturally self-limiting — harder to overdo than liquid additives.
